```

Correct Answer: B

Explanation: The correct approach to add custom data to an order email in Magento 2 using an observer is to use the transportObject. Option B correctly retrieves the transportObject from the event data and uses the setData method to add the custom variable. This ensures that the variable will be available in the email template.

Option A incorrectly attempts to modify the transport directly, which won't work as expected. Option C incorrectly tries to set the data on the order object, which won't make it available in the email template. Option D uses an incorrect method (addData) on the transport object.

